{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:hebrews.3",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "hebrews",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Hebrews 3 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:1",
      "text": "Therefore, holy brethren, who share in a heavenly call, consider Jesus, the apostle and high priest of our confession.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:2",
      "text": "He was faithful to him who appointed him, just as Moses also was faithful in God's house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:3",
      "text": "Yet Jesus has been counted worthy of as much more glory than Moses as the builder of a house has more honor than the house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:4",
      "text": "(For every house is built by some one, but the builder of all things is God.)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:5",
      "text": "Now Moses was faithful in all God's house as a servant, to testify to the things that were to be spoken later,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:6",
      "text": "but Christ was faithful over God's house as a son. And we are his house if we hold fast our confidence and pride in our hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:7",
      "text": "Therefore, as the Holy Spirit says, “Today, when you hear his voice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:8",
      "text": "do not harden your hearts as in the rebellion, on the day of testing in the wilderness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:9",
      "text": "where your fathers put me to the test and saw my works for forty years.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:10",
      "text": "Therefore I was provoked with that generation, and said, ‘They always go astray in their hearts; they have not known my ways.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:11",
      "text": "As I swore in my wrath, ‘They shall never enter my rest.’ ”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:12",
      "text": "Take care, brethren, lest there be in any of you an evil, unbelieving heart, leading you to fall away from the living God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:13",
      "text": "But exhort one another every day, as long as it is called “today,” that none of you may be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:14",
      "text": "For we share in Christ, if only we hold our first confidence firm to the end,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:15",
      "text": "while it is said, “Today, when you hear his voice, do not harden your hearts as in the rebellion.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:16",
      "text": "Who were they that heard and yet were rebellious? Was it not all those who left Egypt under the leadership of Moses?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:17",
      "text": "And with whom was he provoked forty years? Was it not with those who sinned, whose bodies fell in the wilderness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:18",
      "text": "And to whom did he swear that they should never enter his rest, but to those who were disobedient?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:hebrews.3.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:19",
      "text": "So we see that they were unable to enter because of unbelief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
